WEBVTT

00:00:00.660 --> 00:00:04.660
Our focus today is on two beautiful Christian qualities

00:00:04.660 --> 00:00:08.160
that are married to each other, the go hand in hand,

00:00:08.160 --> 00:00:10.660
faith and hope.

00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:15.160
Why is it so important for you and I to strengthen our faith

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:17.160
in what we hope for?

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:21.160
Please open your Bible with me to Hebrews chapter 12

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:24.160
and I'd like you to focus on verse 1.

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:27.160
Of course, we know in the context in the previous chapter,

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:31.160
Hebrews chapter 11, the Apostle has just defined faith

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:35.159
and then went on to recount many examples of men and women

00:00:35.159 --> 00:00:39.659
who exercised strong faith and kept their focus on their future hope.

00:00:39.659 --> 00:00:45.159
And they did so throughout the course of their entire life, even to death.

00:00:45.159 --> 00:00:49.159
But now, notice the exhortation that the Apostle builds on

00:00:49.159 --> 00:00:52.159
as found in Hebrews chapter 12 and verse 1

00:00:52.159 --> 00:00:55.159
and we'll also read the first part of verse 2.

00:00:55.159 --> 00:01:00.159
So then, because we have such a great cloud of witnesses surrounding us,

00:01:00.159 --> 00:01:07.159
let us also throw off every weight and the sin that easily entangles us

00:01:07.159 --> 00:01:11.159
and let us run with endurance, the race that is set before us,

00:01:11.159 --> 00:01:17.159
as we look intently at the chief agent and perfector of our faith, Jesus.

00:01:17.159 --> 00:01:23.159
Now, in verse 1, Paul mentions the sin that easily entangles us.

00:01:23.159 --> 00:01:26.159
What should we visualize?

00:01:26.159 --> 00:01:31.159
Well, that Greek expression could help us to picture a runner in a race

00:01:31.159 --> 00:01:34.159
who has too many clothes on.

00:01:34.159 --> 00:01:38.159
I'm picturing a man who has instead of shorts on,

00:01:38.159 --> 00:01:42.159
he has oversized sweatpants,

00:01:42.159 --> 00:01:46.159
tennis shoes with his shoes unlaced,

00:01:46.159 --> 00:01:50.159
how easy it would be for him to trip and fall

00:01:50.159 --> 00:01:55.159
to be entangled in his own clothing and attire.

00:01:55.159 --> 00:02:01.159
Well, that's the word picture that the Apostle Paul used to describe a danger that faces all of us,

00:02:01.159 --> 00:02:10.159
including experienced Christians who have a record of faith that sin is a lack of faith.

00:02:10.159 --> 00:02:17.159
For a newer Christian, it could be not developing the faith that we had at the beginning

00:02:17.159 --> 00:02:22.159
after baptism, but for an experienced Christian,

00:02:22.159 --> 00:02:29.159
that lack of faith could be a loss of once strong faith we had in the past.

00:02:29.159 --> 00:02:34.159
To that latter point, you might notice in verse 1 that the Apostle Paul,

00:02:34.159 --> 00:02:41.159
a pillar in the congregation, a man of faith, includes himself in the exhortation.

00:02:41.159 --> 00:02:48.159
He says, let us throw off every weight, let us run with endurance.

00:02:48.159 --> 00:02:54.159
By including himself, Paul was likely admitting his own inclination, his propensity,

00:02:54.159 --> 00:03:00.159
to get easily entangled in episodes of momentary weakness of faith.

00:03:00.159 --> 00:03:03.159
Well, that's a powerful lesson for all of us, isn't it?

00:03:03.159 --> 00:03:07.159
All of us need to keep strengthening our faith.

00:03:07.159 --> 00:03:14.159
What is more, the Bible makes it clear that if we get entangled in a momentary loss of faith,

00:03:14.159 --> 00:03:18.159
we can recover, and we can recover quickly.

00:03:18.159 --> 00:03:22.159
Notice this in an experience that the Apostle Peter had.

00:03:22.159 --> 00:03:29.159
Open please with me to Matthew 14 and cast your eyes to verse 24.

00:03:29.159 --> 00:03:33.530
Now visualize the scene.

00:03:33.530 --> 00:03:36.530
It's early in the morning before dawn.

00:03:36.530 --> 00:03:43.530
Peter and some of the disciples are struggling to row their boat in the sea of Galilee during a storm.

00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:46.530
Suddenly they see Jesus walking on the sea.

00:03:46.530 --> 00:03:54.530
In verse 26, when they catch sight of him, the Bible tells us they cried out in their fear.

