00:04:32.529 --> 00:04:34.529
Peter began to sink.

00:04:34.529 --> 00:04:37.529
Why? Notice the opening of verse 30.

00:04:37.529 --> 00:04:42.529
But looking at the wind storm, he became afraid.

00:04:42.529 --> 00:04:47.529
When Peter lost his focus on Jesus, his faith wavered.

00:04:47.529 --> 00:04:51.529
This was a momentary period of weak faith.

00:04:51.529 --> 00:04:55.529
The same can happen to any of us, including experienced Christians.

00:04:55.529 --> 00:05:00.529
The loss of focus can lead to a loss of faith.

00:05:00.529 --> 00:05:05.529
Have you gone through or are going through some storms in your life?

00:05:05.529 --> 00:05:09.529
The wind and the waves that were surrounding Peter as he walked on the water

00:05:09.529 --> 00:05:15.529
could be compared to the trials and the temptations that we face in our dedicated service to Jehovah.

00:05:15.529 --> 00:05:21.529
Thanks to our faith, you and I are doing something that for the majority seems impossible.

00:05:22.529 --> 00:05:26.529
Having a clean standing in a dedicated relationship

00:05:26.529 --> 00:05:30.529
in the last days of this difficult system of things.

00:05:30.529 --> 00:05:33.529
But winds and waves are coming our way.

00:05:33.529 --> 00:05:38.529
