00:05:38.529 --> 00:05:42.529
Maybe it's the fear that comes from the economic pressures

00:05:42.529 --> 00:05:45.529
that are upon many of our brothers and sisters,

00:05:45.529 --> 00:05:49.529
not just in Venezuela, not just in Africa,

00:05:49.529 --> 00:05:54.529
but in all parts of the earth where there's crisis in economies.

00:05:54.529 --> 00:05:59.529
Or maybe it's the waves of persecution that come upon our brothers in all places,

00:05:59.529 --> 00:06:03.529
not just Russia, perhaps right within the family.

00:06:03.529 --> 00:06:08.529
Or what about adjustments that might affect our privileges of service?

00:06:08.529 --> 00:06:13.529
You know, a new work assignment here at Bethel or in the field or in the congregation

00:06:13.529 --> 00:06:20.529
or a change of assignment that takes us out of the comfort zone of special full-time service

00:06:20.529 --> 00:06:26.529
could prove to be a storm for us that causes us to be afraid.

00:06:26.529 --> 00:06:33.529
One brother who had his heart set on being a missionary found that after many years in missionary service,

00:06:33.529 --> 00:06:36.529
he and his wife had to go home.

00:06:36.529 --> 00:06:41.529
For the first time in my life, he says, I lost all sense of direction.

00:06:41.529 --> 00:06:46.529
I had no goals. Nothing seemed important anymore.

00:06:46.529 --> 00:06:48.529
What happened?

00:06:48.529 --> 00:06:53.529
A temporary, momentary weakness and faith.

00:06:53.529 --> 00:06:58.529
But now let's dwell further on Peter's experience as you look back at verse 30.

00:06:58.529 --> 00:07:03.529
What was it specifically that caused Peter to sink?

00:07:03.529 --> 00:07:07.529
Was it a big gust or a big wave?

00:07:07.529 --> 00:07:15.529
No. It was his looking at the windstorm that caused him to become afraid.

00:07:15.529 --> 00:07:18.529
It was his change in focus.

00:07:18.529 --> 00:07:24.529
Likewise, if we lose our focus and dwell too much on our storms,

00:07:24.529 --> 00:07:29.529
circumstances and our day-to-day living in this system of things,

00:07:29.529 --> 00:07:33.529
we look at how powerful those storms are,

00:07:33.529 --> 00:07:37.529
we could begin doubting that Jehovah will support us.

00:07:37.529 --> 00:07:41.529
But now, notice what happens next in verse 30.

00:07:41.529 --> 00:07:47.529
The Bible says, and when he started to sink, he cried out, Lord, save me.

00:07:47.529 --> 00:07:55.529
What Peter did next after his momentary loss of faith is really a powerful lesson for all of us.

00:07:55.529 --> 00:07:57.529
Peter quickly recovered.

00:07:57.529 --> 00:08:01.529
Now, we know from what the Bible tells us that Peter was a capable swimmer.

00:08:01.529 --> 00:08:06.529
